We are given a binary tree as an input and our job is to find if the child nodes are having mirror symmetry for left and right.

We use sub functiond and recursion for this

Step 1: isSymmentric in this we check if tree root == null if yes we return true else we call the sub-function for respose isMirror(root.right , root.left)
Step 2: isMirror : if left and right == null then return true as both does not have chlid nodes so nothing to compare.
Step 3: if either one of left or right != null then there is one chlid but nothing mirroring it so return false.
Step 4: then the actual condiction where we check if left node current value is equal to right node current value 
        and also check the is mirror condition for (left.left, right.right and (left.right and right.left) to recursively verify that child nodes are following the symmetry.


Code:
class Solution {
    public boolean isSymmetric(TreeNode root) {
        
        if(root == null) return true;

        return isMirror(root.left, root.right);
    }

    public boolean isMirror(TreeNode left, TreeNode right)
    {
        if(left == null && right == null) return true;
        if(left == null || right == null) return false;

        return (left.val == right.val) && isMirror(left.left , right.right) && isMirror(left.right , right.left);
    }
}
